headlines.description: — Payton Pritchard finished with his first career triple-double with 30 points, 14 rebounds and 11 assists and the Boston Celtics beat the Atlanta Hawks 120-114 on Sunday in a matchup of mostly reserves in the regular-season finale for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pritchard's triple-double leads Celtics past Hawks, 120-114

headlines.description: — Shake Milton couldn't wait for next weekend. Once Cam Thomas got hot, Milton started competing at a playoff level even in an otherwise meaningless finale.
headlines.shortLinkText: 76ers beat Nets 134-105 before they meet in the playoffs

headlines.description: — Mark Williams had 22 points and 10 rebounds and fellow rookie Bryce McGowens scored 22 points as the Charlotte Hornets rallied in the fourth quarter Sunday for a 106-95 win over the playoff-bound Cleveland Cavaliers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets rally in fourth, beat playoff-bound Cavaliers 106-95

headlines.description: — Udonis Haslem went out a winner, and put on a show.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haslem scores 24 in farewell, Heat top Magic 123-110

events.name: Indiana Pacers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Bennedict Mathurin scored 26 points to lead the Indiana Pacers to a 141-136 win over the New York Knicks on Sunday in the regular season finale for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers outlast Knicks 141-136 in regular season finale

headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. scored 23 points, Precious Achiuwa had 14 points and 13 rebounds and the Toronto Raptors beat the Milwaukee Bucks 121-105 on Sunday in a matchup of short-handed teams whose postseason fates already were sealed.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trent Jr. scores 23, Raptors beat Bucks 121-105 in finale

headlines.description: — Jabari Smith Jr. scored 20 points, and the Houston Rockets went on a 12-0 run late in the fourth quarter to top the Washington Wizards 114-109 on Sunday in the season finale for both.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets rally to top Wizards 114-109 in finale but Silas out

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 17 points and DeMar DeRozan added 16 to help the Bulls end the regular season Sunday with a 103-81 win over the Detroit Pistons.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine, DeRozan put Bulls over Pistons; play-in game next

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving sat for the last two games as part of a plan by the Dallas Mavericks to get back a draft pick sent to the New York Knicks in a trade four years ago.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavs turn focus to Irving after reserve-filled loss to Spurs

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards had 26 points, 13 rebounds, four steals and four blocks to lead Minnesota past New Orleans 113-108 on Sunday, passing the Pelicans in the play-in tournament seeding after losing a pair of starters during the game to <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards leads Wolves rally past Pelicans, after Gobert punch

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Tre Mann notched his first career triple-double, and the Oklahoma City Thunder defeated the Memphis Grizzlies 115-100 on Sunday in the regular-season finale for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mann's triple-double leads Thunder past Grizzlies in finale

headlines.description: — Bruce Brown had a team-high 21 points and six assists, Zeke Nnaji added 18 points and seven rebounds off the bench, and the short-handed Denver Nuggets rallied from a 17-point first-quarter deficit to defeat the Sacramento Kings 109-95 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown, Nnaji lead Nuggets over Kings, end 3-game skid

events.name: Utah Jazz at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James hit eight 3-pointers while scoring 36 points, Anthony Davis had 16 points and 13 rebounds, and the Los Angeles Lakers surged into the postseason as the seventh seed in the Western Conference with a 128-117 victory over the Utah Jazz on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers hold off Jazz 128-117, earn play-in date with Wolves

headlines.description: — The Los Angeles Clippers rallied for a 119-114 win on Sunday over the Phoenix Suns, earning the No. 5 spot in the Western Conference playoff bracket and a first-round rematch against those same Suns.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rally past Suns, secure No. 5 playoff spot in West

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — The Golden State Warriors set an NBA record by scoring 55 points in the first quarter on their way to a 157-101 rout of the Portland Trail Blazers in their regular-season finale on Sunday to secure the sixth seed in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors set NBA record with 55-point 1st quarter in rout
